    // Start streaming with default recommended configuration
    pipe.start(cfg);

    while (waitKey(10))
    {
        auto frameset = pipe.wait_for_frames(); // Wait for next set of frames from the camera
        auto frame = color_map(frameset.get_color_frame());

        // Query frame size (width and height)
        const int w = frame.as<rs2::video_frame>().get_width();
        const int h = frame.as<rs2::video_frame>().get_height();
    }

    return EXIT_SUCCESS;
}
```

Apparently this is caused by

```cpp
    rs2::pipeline pipe;
    // Start streaming with default recommended configuration
    pipe.start();
```

When `pipe.start()` is commented out, the CPU usage falls below 20% (even that's high, but we can come to that at a later stage).

